ON MONDAY EVENING A COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS
CENTRED OVER THE N SEA WITH SECONDARY LOW CENTRES OVER
THE UK. HIGH PRESSURE WILL REMAIN SLOW MOV IN THE
ATLANTIC. THROUGH THE PERIOD COMPLEX FRONTAL TROUGHS WILL
ROTATE AROUND THE MAIN LOW CENTRE WHICH WILL DRIFT SLWY
NWARDS. PRESSURE WILL REMAIN HIGH IN THE ATLANTIC.
OVERNIGHT MONDAY INTO TUESDAY W OR NW GALES WILL AFFECT
ALL PORTPATRICK SEA AREAS EXCEPT IRISH SEA. LATER IN THE
NIGHT THEY WILL EASE W OF 12 W BUT DEVELOP IN THE IRISH
SEA. DURING TUESDAY MORNING NW GALES WILL BECOME CONFINED
TO SEA AREAS LUNDY IRISH SEA AND HEBRIDES. THESE WILL
EASE OVERNIGHT INTO WEDNESDAY. DURING WEDNESDAY STRG
WINDS WILL OCNL TOUCH GALE STRENGTH IN SEA AREAS S E
ICELAND SHANNON AND FAIR ISLE. DURING THE EARLY HOURS OF
THURSDAY GALES BECMG MORE WIDESPREAD IN FAEROES SHANNON
AND ROCKALL AFFECTING FAIR ISLE AT TIMES BEFORE EASING
